<p>The core shift: you stop telling the AI what to do at each step. You tell it what outcome you want. The agent handles the rest.</p>
<h3>The Sense-Think-Act-Learn Framework</h3>
<p>Every agentic marketing system follows a four-stage loop:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Sense.</strong> The agent collects data from CRMs, analytics platforms, ad networks, and customer behavior signals.</li>
<li><strong>Think.</strong> It identifies patterns, segments audiences, and evaluates which action has the highest probability of achieving the goal.</li>
<li><strong>Act.</strong> It executes. Sends the email. Adjusts the bid. Publishes the post. Changes the landing page.</li>
<li><strong>Learn.</strong> It measures the result against the goal and updates its model for the next cycle.</li>
</ol>
<p>This loop runs continuously. Not once a quarter during a strategy review. Not once a week when someone checks the dashboard. Every hour. Every interaction.</p>
