<h2>How to Implement Agentic AI Marketing</h2>
<p>Implementation timelines vary. Teams with clean data and a mature CDP can deploy in 4 to 8 weeks. Teams starting from scratch need 3 to 6 months. Here is the step-by-step path.</p>
<h3>Step 1: Audit Your Data Foundation</h3>
<p>Agentic AI is only as good as the data it operates on. Before selecting any tool, audit:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Customer data completeness.</strong> Do you have unified profiles across channels? Or siloed data in 5 different tools?</li>
<li><strong>Event tracking.</strong> Are you capturing behavioral signals (page views, email opens, purchase history, support tickets)?</li>
<li><strong>Data freshness.</strong> Is your data real-time or updated in weekly batches?</li>
</ul>
<p>If your data is siloed or incomplete, fix that first. No agent can optimize campaigns on bad data.</p>
<h3>Step 2: Identify Your Highest-Value Use Case</h3>
<p>Do not try to automate everything at once. Pick one use case with clear, measurable outcomes:</p>
